1
00:00:40,839 --> 00:00:48,479
This film contains very strong language and some violent scenes

2
00:00:54,359 --> 00:00:55,679
Nice shot, Hamb.

3
00:00:55,679 --> 00:00:58,079
I drilled a little to the left.

4
00:00:58,079 --> 00:01:00,279
It's 15 feet from the goddamn hole.

5
00:01:01,199 --> 00:01:03,519
I miscalculated the wind by a couple knots.

6
00:01:03,519 --> 00:01:04,599
Give me a break.

7
00:01:04,599 --> 00:01:06,719
Well, you know, it's all a matter of degrees.

8
00:01:06,719 --> 00:01:09,879
The difference between the big money and not making the cut is razor-thin.

9
00:01:12,359 --> 00:01:15,439
Well, I wasn't thinking about qualifying for the Masters.

10
00:01:15,439 --> 00:01:18,279
Kind of had my sights set on the NBA.

11
00:01:18,279 --> 00:01:22,119
HELICOPTER WHIRRS OVERHEAD

12
00:01:29,119 --> 00:01:30,919
Well, your hook shot's working, Scotty.

13
00:01:46,759 --> 00:01:48,239
Nice shot.

14
00:01:53,439 --> 00:01:56,399
What do you think I'm doing wrong here?

15
00:01:58,239 --> 00:02:01,159
I think you're standing too close to the ball.

16
00:02:01,159 --> 00:02:02,599
Yeah. Pretty bad, huh?

17
00:02:02,599 --> 00:02:03,999
After you hit it.

18
00:02:03,999 --> 00:02:05,039
..Yeah?

19
00:02:05,039 --> 00:02:07,879
They want you at ops right away, sir.

20
00:04:23,999 --> 00:04:29,519
- MAN:
- Russian tanks, 8-inch guns, and APCs.

21
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:32,119
Seventh Air Force intelligence has been indicating

22
00:04:32,119 --> 00:04:34,799
the possibility of a North Vietnamese/VC offensive.

23
00:04:34,799 --> 00:04:36,759
Now, these photos confirm it.

24
00:04:38,159 --> 00:04:41,719
NVA troops moving down the Ho Chi Minh Trail,

25
00:04:41,719 --> 00:04:46,159
south of the DMZ, near Quang Tri.

26
00:04:46,159 --> 00:04:47,919
Now, they'll combine with Charlie

27
00:04:47,919 --> 00:04:50,799
and try to hit us hard,

28
00:04:50,799 --> 00:04:53,119
probably in several places at once.

29
00:04:54,079 --> 00:04:56,079
Glad you could make it, Colonel.

30
00:04:56,079 --> 00:04:57,879
Sorry, sir.

31
00:04:59,839 --> 00:05:02,119
Strategic Air Command's putting everything it's got

32
00:05:02,119 --> 00:05:05,119
in the air two days from now and will just clobber the hell out of them.

33
00:05:05,119 --> 00:05:07,439
If we don't stop their movement,

34
00:05:07,439 --> 00:05:10,439
or at least slow it down to a trickle,

35
00:05:10,439 --> 00:05:12,839
our ground troops are going to take heavy casualties.

36
00:05:12,839 --> 00:05:15,479
Now, our job remains the same,

37
00:05:15,479 --> 00:05:18,319
fly alongside the bombers,

38
00:05:18,319 --> 00:05:20,479
throw down your electronic smoke screens,

39
00:05:20,479 --> 00:05:22,559
jam the missile radars.

40
00:05:22,559 --> 00:05:25,279
Sir, why don't we put our surveillance aircraft up there first, sir?

41
00:05:25,279 --> 00:05:28,519
Have them fly the same route the big boys are going to fly on their scheduled run.

42
00:05:28,519 --> 00:05:30,079
Missile reaction can be recorded,

43
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:33,039
launch sites plotted.

44
00:05:33,039 --> 00:05:35,999
Send the fighter jocks in there to just knock the hell out of them.

45
00:05:51,719 --> 00:05:55,199
I really appreciate you volunteering us for this flight, Hamb.

46
00:05:55,199 --> 00:05:57,919
Didn't think you had your sights set on being a full bird.

47
00:05:57,919 --> 00:06:00,319
I've got my sights set on a condo

48
00:06:00,319 --> 00:06:03,199
on the seventh fairway at Tucson National.

49
00:06:03,199 --> 00:06:06,079
Six months from now, that's where the old lady and me will be.

50
00:06:06,079 --> 00:06:08,479
That sounds awfully exciting(!)

51
00:06:08,479 --> 00:06:11,479
You think that's exciting?

52
00:06:11,479 --> 00:06:13,079
You should see the deck furniture.

53
00:06:13,079 --> 00:06:15,239
Ha!

54
00:06:23,519 --> 00:06:25,999
Mark. Start your music.

55
00:06:28,159 --> 00:06:30,079
I've got a solid growl.

56
00:06:30,079 --> 00:06:32,359
SAM on scope. I confirm a launch.

57
00:06:32,359 --> 00:06:34,599
I got him.

58
00:06:38,479 --> 00:06:41,079
Goddamn it. I didn't think they had SAMs this far south.

59
00:06:41,079 --> 00:06:42,999
That's why we're here.

60
00:06:42,999 --> 00:06:45,519
Have to go back and give them the bad news.

61
00:06:45,519 --> 00:06:47,519
I've got another one.

62
00:06:47,519 --> 00:06:49,359
SAM on scope. 2, salvo 3.

63
00:06:49,359 --> 00:06:53,159
They're changing frequencies. I've got one.

64
00:06:53,159 --> 00:06:56,079
Hold it steady. Got two.

65
00:06:56,079 --> 00:06:57,919
- Got one visual.
- Break left!

66
00:06:57,919 --> 00:07:00,079
Break left! LOUD BUZZING

67
00:07:00,079 --> 00:07:02,639
It's tracking us! It's locked!

68
00:07:06,519 --> 00:07:09,919
We're hit! Everybody get out!

69
00:07:09,919 --> 00:07:12,039
We're going down!

70
00:07:12,039 --> 00:07:13,079
We're burning up!

71
00:07:14,159 --> 00:07:17,519
Hit by SAM! Mayday! Mayday!

72
00:07:17,519 --> 00:07:19,439
I've lost it. Crew eject! Crew eject!

73
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:21,119
I can't get out!

74
00:07:21,119 --> 00:07:23,759
Red Scout One hit by SAMs!

75
00:07:23,759 --> 00:07:25,199
Punch out, Hamb!

76
00:07:25,199 --> 00:07:26,639
Come on, Scotty! Let's get out!

77
00:07:26,639 --> 00:07:28,039
Right behind you!

78
00:07:28,039 --> 00:07:29,199
Mayday! Mayday!

79
00:07:39,239 --> 00:07:42,159
Punch out, Scotty! Somebody punch out!

80
00:07:54,919 --> 00:07:58,759
RADIO: 'Recon pilots in quadrant Lima-Charlie-Six,

81
00:07:58,759 --> 00:08:02,519
'Mayday transmitted by Red Scout EB-66.

82
00:08:02,519 --> 00:08:03,719
'Look for smoke and chutes.

83
00:08:03,719 --> 00:08:06,119
'Repeat, look for smoke and chutes.'

84
00:08:06,119 --> 00:08:07,439
Roger.

85
00:08:10,719 --> 00:08:14,359
HAMBLETON ON RADIO: 02 FAC! 02, come in!

86
00:08:14,359 --> 00:08:18,079
This is FAC 02, call sign Birddog.

87
00:08:18,079 --> 00:08:19,719
Identify yourself.

88
00:08:19,719 --> 00:08:23,359
Bat 21. I'm the parachute above you, one o'clock.

89
00:08:23,359 --> 00:08:24,919
BEEPING

90
00:08:24,919 --> 00:08:29,279
Have you in sight. Turn off your beeper, Bat 21,

91
00:08:29,279 --> 00:08:32,039
or Charlie will get to you before the Jolly Greens.

92
00:08:32,039 --> 00:08:34,279
Will advise. Happy landings.

93
00:08:34,279 --> 00:08:35,759
Roger.

94
00:09:15,679 --> 00:09:17,879
Bat 21, get out of that paddy!

95
00:09:17,879 --> 00:09:20,279
Hooches to the south. Head north to the tree line.

96
00:09:20,279 --> 00:09:23,159
Repeat, head north to the tree line.

97
00:09:31,359 --> 00:09:34,159
Repeat, tree line north. Roger that?

98
00:09:34,159 --> 00:09:36,559
Negative. I want to wait for the choppers.

99
00:09:36,559 --> 00:09:37,919
Negative.

100
00:09:37,919 --> 00:09:39,919
Let's get the basic relationship down here.

101
00:09:39,919 --> 00:09:43,559
I'm the lifeguard. You're the drowning man.

102
00:09:43,559 --> 00:09:45,919
If you relax, I can bring you to shore.

103
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:48,079
If you fight me, then I'll have to slap you around.

104
00:09:48,079 --> 00:09:50,159
Now, get your ass in gear, mister!

105
00:09:59,439 --> 00:10:02,279
Bat 21, Charlie's firing mortars from the south.

106
00:10:02,279 --> 00:10:04,799
Advise at tree line. Repeat, advise at tree line.

107
00:10:55,199 --> 00:10:57,159
PLANE APPROACHES

108
00:10:58,559 --> 00:11:01,799
Birddog, this is Bat 21. I can't go any further.

109
00:11:01,799 --> 00:11:03,319
Get the helis from this position.

110
00:11:03,319 --> 00:11:06,239
- Copy, Bat 21.
- What about the others?

111
00:11:06,239 --> 00:11:07,839
Anybody else make it out?

112
00:11:07,839 --> 00:11:10,559
None reported. We're still looking.

113
00:11:10,559 --> 00:11:12,519
Just stay calm.

114
00:11:12,519 --> 00:11:14,919
I'll try.

115
00:11:14,919 --> 00:11:18,039
Don't worry, Bat 21. We'll get you out.

116
00:11:18,039 --> 00:11:20,199
But it's not going to happen today.

117
00:11:20,199 --> 00:11:23,119
All choppers busy evac-ing fire base at Quang Tri.

118
00:11:23,119 --> 00:11:25,519
Company of guns overrun by Charlie.

119
00:11:25,519 --> 00:11:28,399
Jolly Greens will pick you up in the morning.

120
00:11:37,559 --> 00:11:40,359
Say again, your last transmission.

121
00:11:40,359 --> 00:11:44,639
Repeat, Jolly Greens will pick you up in the morning.

122
00:11:44,639 --> 00:11:48,439
There will be no pick-up today. Copy, Bat 21?

123
00:11:48,439 --> 00:11:50,439
EXPLOSIONS IN THE DISTANCE

124
00:11:51,879 --> 00:11:53,759
I copy, Birddog.

125
00:11:53,759 --> 00:11:55,719
OK, listen, Bat 21.

126
00:11:55,719 --> 00:12:00,359
I'm running low on juice. Have to return to base.

127
00:12:00,359 --> 00:12:02,359
Birddog, thanks for your help.

128
00:12:02,359 --> 00:12:04,759
That's what I'm here for.

129
00:12:04,759 --> 00:12:06,719
Birddog, you going to be back?

130
00:12:06,719 --> 00:12:08,239
That's the plan.

131
00:12:08,239 --> 00:12:11,719
Birddog signing off. Keep your head down. See you later.

132
00:12:12,839 --> 00:12:14,999
Bat 21 out.

133
00:12:14,999 --> 00:12:16,919
PLANE FADES INTO DISTANCE

134
00:12:42,679 --> 00:12:44,599
THEY SPEAK IN VIETNAMESE

135
00:13:15,359 --> 00:13:17,199
SITAR MUSIC PLAYS

136
00:13:20,039 --> 00:13:21,999
HE CHANTS

137
00:13:47,319 --> 00:13:48,359
How was your flight, sir?

138
00:13:48,359 --> 00:13:53,159
Same old shit, bad movies and terrible food.

139
00:13:53,159 --> 00:13:57,319
Don't you, uh... don't you think

140
00:13:57,319 --> 00:13:58,839
you're pushing it a little, Captain?

141
00:13:58,839 --> 00:14:02,239
You've almost doubled the base record.

142
00:14:02,239 --> 00:14:03,719
The base record? Sheesh!

143
00:14:03,719 --> 00:14:05,599
I'll pin a medal on my chest(!)

144
00:14:05,599 --> 00:14:07,999
Would you check my right aileron?

145
00:14:07,999 --> 00:14:10,639
It's sticking a bit, OK?

146
00:14:13,759 --> 00:14:15,719
Yeah, I got to replace it, sir.

147
00:14:15,719 --> 00:14:18,119
How long will that take?

148
00:14:18,119 --> 00:14:22,519
Well, I can borrow one from 453.

149
00:14:22,519 --> 00:14:25,679
That's Anderson's ship.

150
00:14:25,679 --> 00:14:28,479
The way he flies, Captain, he'll never miss it, sir.

151
00:14:28,479 --> 00:14:33,159
Ha-ha-ha! I like your initiative, Sergeant.

152
00:14:33,159 --> 00:14:34,879
Keep it up.

153
00:14:36,439 --> 00:14:39,119
Well, we've pulled our share of pilots out of there,

154
00:14:39,119 --> 00:14:41,519
but never a 53-year-old Lieutenant Colonel.

155
00:14:41,519 --> 00:14:45,319
A 53-year-old Lieutenant Colonel?

156
00:14:45,319 --> 00:14:48,319
That's right. Navigator on that EB.

157
00:14:49,679 --> 00:14:52,079
They just gave me crew codes

158
00:14:52,079 --> 00:14:54,039
and no names and ranks.

159
00:14:54,039 --> 00:14:56,959
Well, I am told that Hambleton

160
00:14:56,959 --> 00:14:58,359
is one of our top people.

161
00:14:58,359 --> 00:15:00,239
He's an electronics countermeasure expert.

162
00:15:00,239 --> 00:15:02,999
I am told that the Communists

163
00:15:02,999 --> 00:15:05,319
will have a dossier on him that thick.

164
00:15:05,319 --> 00:15:07,799
So, in the morning, when we get our birds back,

165
00:15:07,799 --> 00:15:09,119
we're going to go in and get him.

166
00:15:09,119 --> 00:15:10,799
Seventh Air Force does not want Charlie

167
00:15:10,799 --> 00:15:12,679
getting their hands on him.

168
00:15:12,679 --> 00:15:14,639
We'll get him tomorrow then, sir.

169
00:15:14,639 --> 00:15:16,079
In the meantime, I want you

170
00:15:16,079 --> 00:15:17,479
to go back out there tonight.

171
00:15:17,479 --> 00:15:19,079
But he's not going anywhere, Colonel.

172
00:15:19,079 --> 00:15:22,279
I know, because I'm going to make damn certain he's secure.

173
00:15:22,279 --> 00:15:23,679
Then why don't you send Anderson?

174
00:15:23,679 --> 00:15:26,119
Didn't he just get his pilot's licence?

175
00:15:26,119 --> 00:15:28,519
You'd better watch it, Captain.

176
00:15:28,519 --> 00:15:31,399
Look, sir, I'm tired, I'm two weeks short,

177
00:15:31,399 --> 00:15:33,799
and that area is pretty hot,

178
00:15:33,799 --> 00:15:35,679
and I don't want to get shot down

179
00:15:35,679 --> 00:15:38,639
on some public-relations mission, OK?

180
00:15:42,439 --> 00:15:45,279
All right, then, I'll make it easy for you, Captain.

181
00:15:45,279 --> 00:15:48,079
It's an order, and you damn well will carry it out.

182
00:15:48,079 --> 00:15:50,119
Is that clear?

183
00:15:52,839 --> 00:15:54,479
Yes, sir.

184
00:15:59,239 --> 00:16:01,679
Thank you for the ride, sir.

185
00:16:59,079 --> 00:17:00,639
TWIG SNAPS

186
00:17:59,639 --> 00:18:03,039
MEN SPEAK SOFTLY IN VIETNAMESE

187
00:18:43,399 --> 00:18:44,919
BRANCH SNAPS

188
00:19:34,559 --> 00:19:37,039
Phew! OK...

189
00:19:37,039 --> 00:19:38,959
50 piasters.

190
00:19:38,959 --> 00:19:40,399
THE OTHER MEN GROAN

191
00:19:40,399 --> 00:19:42,319
Come on! Chickenshits! Chickenshits!

192
00:19:42,319 --> 00:19:43,759
No way.

193
00:19:43,759 --> 00:19:45,679
OK. Hey, Clarky, pull up a chair,

194
00:19:45,679 --> 00:19:47,599
before these pigeons are totally penniless.

195
00:19:47,599 --> 00:19:50,479
Another time. I got to go back up again tonight.

196
00:19:50,479 --> 00:19:51,919
Going back up again?

197
00:19:51,919 --> 00:19:53,839
Damn, putting in the hours.

198
00:19:53,839 --> 00:19:55,279
Yeah. Tell Walker.

199
00:19:55,279 --> 00:19:58,119
I got to start carrying my sleeping bag with me.

200
00:19:58,119 --> 00:20:00,039
OK... I got two pair.

201
00:20:00,039 --> 00:20:02,559
Three sixes.

202
00:20:02,559 --> 00:20:05,319
I've got two pairs of sevens and your other six.

203
00:20:05,319 --> 00:20:06,639
Ha-ha-ha!

204
00:20:06,639 --> 00:20:09,719
Damn! I thought you newspaper boys

205
00:20:09,719 --> 00:20:12,279
would be a bit sharper than that. What rag do you write for again?

206
00:20:12,279 --> 00:20:13,919
New York Times.

207
00:20:13,919 --> 00:20:15,839
Oh, yeah, I picked one up once.

208
00:20:15,839 --> 00:20:18,759
You read, Ross? Probably stole it from some derelict in the park,

209
00:20:18,759 --> 00:20:20,199
who was using it as a blanket.

210
00:20:20,199 --> 00:20:21,639
I gave him a nickel!

211
00:20:21,639 --> 00:20:24,399
I couldn't find the comics, so I returned it.

212
00:20:24,399 --> 00:20:25,959
Did you get your money back?

213
00:20:25,959 --> 00:20:28,519
Yeah. I ended up finishing a pint of radiator fluid with the guy.

214
00:20:28,519 --> 00:20:30,599
It was about then I figured it was time to enlist,

215
00:20:30,599 --> 00:20:33,599
and here I am, the best goddamn evac pilot in 'Nam!

216
00:20:33,599 --> 00:20:35,039
Tell it, Ross.

217
00:20:35,039 --> 00:20:38,399
Flying those choppers every day scrambles up your brains. You get facts confused.

218
00:20:38,399 --> 00:20:40,319
Ross here thinks that it takes some skill

219
00:20:40,319 --> 00:20:42,239
to keep one of those eggbeaters up in the air.

220
00:20:42,239 --> 00:20:43,599
Typical FAC pilot.

221
00:20:43,599 --> 00:20:45,199
He labours under the misapprehension

222
00:20:45,199 --> 00:20:47,519
that he is the most Sierra-Hotel cowboy in the Air Force.

223
00:20:47,519 --> 00:20:48,999
The real truth is, he flies

224
00:20:48,999 --> 00:20:50,879
a fucking VW Microbus with wings.

225
00:20:50,879 --> 00:20:53,239
Well, this VW pilot

226
00:20:53,239 --> 00:20:55,199
flies ten feet off the deck,

227
00:20:55,199 --> 00:20:57,799
draws fire from SAMs down to eight-year-olds

228
00:20:57,799 --> 00:20:59,239
with slingshots and pebbles.

229
00:20:59,239 --> 00:21:02,319
Ha-ha-ha! A confirmation on that.

230
00:21:02,319 --> 00:21:03,599
A lot of times, I've seen Clark

231
00:21:03,599 --> 00:21:05,159
return here... You want one?

232
00:21:05,159 --> 00:21:06,319
..with leaves in his teeth.

233
00:21:06,319 --> 00:21:07,359
Because...

234
00:21:07,359 --> 00:21:08,399
Two.

235
00:21:08,399 --> 00:21:10,679
..us black folks ain't got no depth perception.

236
00:21:10,679 --> 00:21:12,719
So we gots to fly what we gets.

237
00:21:12,719 --> 00:21:14,359
MEN LAUGH

238
00:21:14,359 --> 00:21:16,999
They won't let us fly fast aeroplanes!

239
00:21:16,999 --> 00:21:20,559
You got to be particular in this man's Air Force.

240
00:21:20,559 --> 00:21:24,999
Now, right here, you are looking at a perfect flyboy profile.

241
00:21:24,999 --> 00:21:28,519
The kind of guy you can trust when the shit hits the fan.

242
00:21:28,519 --> 00:21:31,399
Boom. It's hit the fan, man!

243
00:21:35,799 --> 00:21:37,279
See you later, Clarky.

244
00:21:37,279 --> 00:21:39,319
Later, Clarky.

245
00:21:39,319 --> 00:21:42,599
Don't wait up for me, OK?

246
00:21:42,599 --> 00:21:44,639
Take care.

247
00:21:50,199 --> 00:21:53,239
PLANE FLIES OVERHEAD

248
00:21:57,039 --> 00:22:00,399
Birddog, Bat 21. Is that you?

249
00:22:00,399 --> 00:22:03,639
Roger, Bat 21. It's me.

250
00:22:03,639 --> 00:22:07,559
I need a visual reference, so I can stay in range.

251
00:22:07,559 --> 00:22:09,559
You'll need one.

252
00:22:31,359 --> 00:22:32,799
Got you, Bat 21.

253
00:22:32,799 --> 00:22:35,359
Positive contact.

254
00:22:41,439 --> 00:22:44,999
I appreciate you dropping by, Birddog.

255
00:22:44,999 --> 00:22:47,399
That's what I'm here for.

256
00:22:47,399 --> 00:22:52,799
Charlie walked by my hole about an hour ago.

257
00:22:52,799 --> 00:22:54,599
How many?

258
00:22:54,599 --> 00:22:59,399
10 or 12. It seems to be quiet now.

259
00:22:59,399 --> 00:23:01,599
Just stay calm.

260
00:23:01,599 --> 00:23:04,239
You'll be out of there in the morning.

261
00:23:05,639 --> 00:23:08,999
