01:05:23,359 --> 01:05:24,919
Don't leave us, Ross!

789
01:05:24,919 --> 01:05:27,279
Don't worry. I'll be back.

790
01:05:27,279 --> 01:05:29,999
All right!

791
01:05:29,999 --> 01:05:32,119
SHOUTING CONTINUES

792
01:05:34,719 --> 01:05:36,879
Ross! Ross!

793
01:05:36,879 --> 01:05:39,319
GUNFIRE

794
01:05:39,319 --> 01:05:41,679
Goddamn you!

795
01:06:31,559 --> 01:06:33,879
Birddog, they've got two of our men.

796
01:06:33,879 --> 01:06:36,799
I think the rest of the crew is dead.

797
01:06:36,799 --> 01:06:38,719
Uh, copy, Bat 21. Stand by.

798
01:06:38,719 --> 01:06:40,759
Cobra Leader, Charlie has two of our airmen.

799
01:06:40,759 --> 01:06:42,559
Can you identify?

800
01:06:42,559 --> 01:06:45,919
Negative, Birddog. Can't make out from here.

801
01:06:45,919 --> 01:06:48,319
We're holding our fire.

802
01:06:48,319 --> 01:06:51,999
They shot my damn hydraulics out.

803
01:06:51,999 --> 01:06:55,559
I'm not going to be able to put this thing down here.

804
01:06:55,559 --> 01:06:57,439
I'm going down for a closer look.

805
01:06:57,439 --> 01:06:58,879
Not advisable, Birddog.

806
01:06:58,879 --> 01:07:00,959
It will be a quick pass.

807
01:07:06,319 --> 01:07:09,239
GUNFIRE

808
01:07:11,999 --> 01:07:13,599
Confirmed, two airmen.

809
01:07:13,599 --> 01:07:15,759
One is pilot.

810
01:07:25,799 --> 01:07:27,759
THEY SPEAK IN VIETNAMESE

811
01:07:29,999 --> 01:07:32,519
You know what, Charlie? I don't follow your fucking drift.

812
01:07:32,519 --> 01:07:34,919
I took Spanish in school. No comprendo.

813
01:07:34,919 --> 01:07:37,079
HE SHOUTS IN VIETNAMESE

814
01:07:37,079 --> 01:07:41,159
Get your fucking slimy fucking hands off me!

815
01:07:43,519 --> 01:07:47,239
I don't know what the fuck you're talking about!

816
01:07:47,239 --> 01:07:49,759
I don't understand you.

817
01:07:49,759 --> 01:07:53,959
Birddog, they're trying to get him to tell where I am.

818
01:07:53,959 --> 01:07:56,519
Copy, Bat 21. Just stay low.

819
01:08:08,119 --> 01:08:10,079
GUNSHOT

820
01:08:10,079 --> 01:08:12,359
Bastard! Motherfucker!

821
01:08:25,719 --> 01:08:28,199
They just killed one of our men.

822
01:08:28,199 --> 01:08:30,879
Was it the pilot, Bat 21?

823
01:08:30,879 --> 01:08:33,439
I don't think so. It's me they want.

824
01:08:33,439 --> 01:08:35,599
I'm going to give myself up.

825
01:08:35,599 --> 01:08:38,359
Keep your ass down, Bat 21! Charlie doesn't bargain.

826
01:08:38,359 --> 01:08:40,119
Nothing you can do about it.

827
01:08:40,119 --> 01:08:43,079
Now, retreat double-time back into the trees.

828
01:09:06,879 --> 01:09:08,159
Come on, fella. Come closer.

829
01:09:08,159 --> 01:09:10,359
Come on. Come on, you motherfucker.

830
01:09:10,359 --> 01:09:12,279
Come on.

831
01:09:12,279 --> 01:09:14,199
Oh!

832
01:09:14,199 --> 01:09:15,679
HE IMITATES AN EXPLOSION

833
01:09:17,079 --> 01:09:18,559
Come on.

834
01:09:18,559 --> 01:09:21,359
They're walking him out into the minefield.

835
01:09:21,359 --> 01:09:23,319
Ah, Jesus!

836
01:09:26,639 --> 01:09:28,599
Come on!

837
01:10:06,439 --> 01:10:09,319
Hey, come on!

838
01:10:09,319 --> 01:10:10,359
Agh!

839
01:10:11,719 --> 01:10:14,079
ROSS SCREAMS

840
01:10:14,079 --> 01:10:17,599
Aah! Aah!

841
01:10:19,599 --> 01:10:20,799
Goddamn it!

842
01:10:30,039 --> 01:10:33,119
Aah!

843
01:10:46,679 --> 01:10:48,639
Motherfucker!

844
01:10:50,639 --> 01:10:53,679
You lowlife...

845
01:11:09,399 --> 01:11:13,559
I've got enough dead heroes for one day, Clark!

846
01:11:13,559 --> 01:11:15,959
Get your ass out of there!

847
01:11:15,959 --> 01:11:18,159
Oh, fuck.

848
01:11:23,839 --> 01:11:26,519
You'll get Bat 21 back on the course!

849
01:11:26,519 --> 01:11:30,999
Then rendezvous with me at Hilo-1-8-5.

850
01:11:30,999 --> 01:11:33,959
I'm going to waste this whole goddamned area!

851
01:11:43,959 --> 01:11:48,759
Four-square leader, hustle your ass over here.

852
01:11:48,759 --> 01:11:52,439
One click north of Hilo-1-niner-6.

853
01:11:52,439 --> 01:11:54,839
Gun emplacement in village.

854
01:11:54,839 --> 01:11:59,119
Jolly Green down. Crew is dead.

855
01:11:59,119 --> 01:12:02,119
Look for the smoke.

856
01:12:06,279 --> 01:12:08,239
People are still in the village.

857
01:12:08,239 --> 01:12:10,159
Charlie is using them for cover.

858
01:12:10,159 --> 01:12:12,559
Stay off frequency, Bat 21.

859
01:12:12,559 --> 01:12:14,919
Await instructions from Birddog.

860
01:12:21,199 --> 01:12:25,039
Birddog. Birddog, people are in the village.

861
01:12:25,039 --> 01:12:28,719
Repeat, civilians, women and children, in the village.

862
01:12:28,719 --> 01:12:31,319
That's a confirmation. Will advise.

863
01:12:33,199 --> 01:12:35,839
Cobra Leader, this is Birddog.

864
01:12:35,839 --> 01:12:37,359
Village is still not clear.

865
01:12:37,359 --> 01:12:38,879
Civilians still in area.

866
01:12:38,879 --> 01:12:41,519
Stay off frequency.

867
01:12:41,519 --> 01:12:43,719
Delay the strike. Repeat, delay strike.

868
01:12:43,719 --> 01:12:46,999
Bat 21, get back on course.

869
01:12:46,999 --> 01:12:48,719
Will connect with you at swanee.

870
01:12:48,719 --> 01:12:51,639
Fuck the goddamn swanee. Delay the strike!

871
01:12:51,639 --> 01:12:53,319
That was my friend laying in the mud

872
01:12:53,319 --> 01:12:55,079
with his fucking head blown off!

873
01:12:55,079 --> 01:12:56,479
Now, get back on course!

874
01:12:56,479 --> 01:12:59,119
Now, do as I say! Back on course!

875
01:13:58,999 --> 01:14:01,919
People keep dying all around me.

876
01:14:06,679 --> 01:14:09,119
I'm through killing.

877
01:14:10,519 --> 01:14:12,959
I'm through, goddamn it.

878
01:14:58,479 --> 01:14:59,959
HE SIGHS

879
01:15:02,799 --> 01:15:04,879
You called for me, sir?

880
01:15:08,519 --> 01:15:09,999
Ahem...

881
01:15:09,999 --> 01:15:12,399
Lost six people today, Clark.

882
01:15:12,399 --> 01:15:14,919
Kids, all of them, just kids.

883
01:15:16,679 --> 01:15:18,999
And I couldn't guarantee

884
01:15:18,999 --> 01:15:20,479
we'd get him out of there

885
01:15:20,479 --> 01:15:22,239
if we had another week. Damn it, it's too hot.

886
01:15:22,239 --> 01:15:25,279
HE SIGHS

887
01:15:25,279 --> 01:15:28,639
So, the strike is a go...

888
01:15:28,639 --> 01:15:31,039
07:00 hours tomorrow.

889
01:15:31,039 --> 01:15:33,919
They're going to level the whole area.

890
01:15:33,919 --> 01:15:36,319
All we can do is hope and pray to God

891
01:15:36,319 --> 01:15:39,199
Hambleton makes it to the river.

892
01:15:39,199 --> 01:15:41,079
I, uh...

893
01:15:41,079 --> 01:15:43,959
Did I ever call the Navy,

894
01:15:43,959 --> 01:15:46,399
and, uh, they're going to send

895
01:15:46,399 --> 01:15:48,399
a patrol boat up there.

896
01:15:50,239 --> 01:15:52,199
Where are you headed?

897
01:15:53,599 --> 01:15:56,279
I'm going to help him make it to the river, sir.

898
01:15:57,759 --> 01:15:59,799
Planes are grounded, Clark.

899
01:15:59,799 --> 01:16:02,519
We are not to go back in there

900
01:16:02,519 --> 01:16:04,319
until the strike is over.

901
01:16:05,719 --> 01:16:08,439
Our hands are tied.

902
01:16:08,439 --> 01:16:10,399
Yes, sir.

903
01:16:22,839 --> 01:16:24,319
HE SIGHS

904
01:17:08,839 --> 01:17:11,759
Birddog, Bat 21. Over.

905
01:17:13,639 --> 01:17:16,999
Birddog, Bat 21. How do you read? Over.

906
01:17:16,999 --> 01:17:20,359
'Birddog, this is Bat 21. Come in.

907
01:17:20,359 --> 01:17:23,239
'I'm on the sixth hole, Birddog. Do you copy?

908
01:17:23,239 --> 01:17:25,679
'Birddog, this is Bat 21.

909
01:17:27,079 --> 01:17:29,079
'Come in, Birddog.'

910
01:18:32,279 --> 01:18:33,719
Thank you.

911
01:18:49,559 --> 01:18:51,199
For me?

912
01:18:53,839 --> 01:18:55,839
BOY SPEAKS IN VIETNAMESE

913
01:21:09,599 --> 01:21:12,919
Definitely not a good idea, sir. It's a bad idea.

914
01:21:12,919 --> 01:21:14,839
I trained in one of these things 15 years ago.

915
01:21:14,839 --> 01:21:16,799
So, just refresh my memory.

916
01:21:16,799 --> 01:21:18,279
You got three minutes.

917
01:21:21,599 --> 01:21:23,479
Let's go, Rumbaugh.

918
01:21:23,479 --> 01:21:24,839
All right.

919
01:21:24,839 --> 01:21:25,959
OK.

920
01:21:25,959 --> 01:21:28,279
This is your rotor speed. Keep it in the green.

921
01:21:28,279 --> 01:21:29,719
This is your engine speed.

922
01:21:29,719 --> 01:21:31,199
Keep it also in the green.

923
01:21:31,199 --> 01:21:33,039
Red-line and you crash and burn.

924
01:21:33,039 --> 01:21:35,439
All right, pedals. Pedals work the same as your ship.

925
01:21:35,439 --> 01:21:37,399
The stick does not. It's cyclic.

926
01:21:37,399 --> 01:21:39,479
It controls the angles of your blades, all right?

927
01:21:39,479 --> 01:21:42,199
I can't believe you're taking the old man's ship.

928
01:21:42,199 --> 01:21:44,879
All right, power. Power's controlled by your collective.

929
01:21:44,879 --> 01:21:46,359
One thing you may have forgotten is,

930
01:21:46,359 --> 01:21:48,879
when you increase power, you increase left pedal

931
01:21:48,879 --> 01:21:52,239
to compensate for increased torque. Got it?

932
01:21:52,239 --> 01:21:56,079
Yeah, um...yeah, it's coming back to me.

933
01:21:56,079 --> 01:21:58,679
And what about autorotation?

934
01:21:58,679 --> 01:22:00,519
Why? You planning on not coming back, sir?

935
01:22:00,519 --> 01:22:03,279
Tell me anyway.

936
01:22:03,279 --> 01:22:06,799
All right. Your engine quits.

937
01:22:06,799 --> 01:22:08,039
You're falling out of the sky.

938
01:22:08,039 --> 01:22:11,999
Now, all you've got left is the energy stored in your blades, OK?

939
01:22:11,999 --> 01:22:13,599
Push the left...

940
01:22:13,599 --> 01:22:16,799
No, push the right, the right pedal to the floor,

941
01:22:16,799 --> 01:22:18,519
collective down,

942
01:22:18,519 --> 01:22:20,639
keep your rotor speed in the green.

943
01:22:20,639 --> 01:22:24,519
Keep it at about 80 knots and about 100 feet off the deck.

944
01:22:24,519 --> 01:22:27,319
Begin to flare and then cushion it on down with the collective.

945
01:22:27,319 --> 01:22:29,719
Now, you may start to spin,

946
01:22:29,719 --> 01:22:31,959
but that's cool. Don't panic.

947
01:22:31,959 --> 01:22:34,079
Key point being, he who hesitates...

948
01:22:34,079 --> 01:22:35,999
You don't want to hesitate, all right?

949
01:22:35,999 --> 01:22:37,439
All right.

950
01:22:37,439 --> 01:22:40,279
Here's your checklist, your maps, all your golf shit.

951
01:22:40,279 --> 01:22:41,719
All right.

952
01:22:41,719 --> 01:22:43,159
Now, you got everything, right?

953
01:22:43,159 --> 01:22:44,719
You understand all this?

954
01:22:44,719 --> 01:22:45,759
Yeah.

955
01:22:45,759 --> 01:22:46,999
All right.

956
01:22:46,999 --> 01:22:48,439
Thanks for the lesson.

957
01:22:48,439 --> 01:22:49,599
Just come back, all right?

958
01:23:05,399 --> 01:23:07,759
Pedals! Pedals!

959
01:23:10,119 --> 01:23:11,959
Collective!

960
01:23:11,959 --> 01:23:13,839
Shit!

961
01:23:13,839 --> 01:23:16,159
Up! Up! Up!

962
01:23:17,919 --> 01:23:22,439
OK, all right. Torque, torque, torque.

963
01:23:24,919 --> 01:23:26,679
Get it up!

964
01:23:26,679 --> 01:23:30,199
You got it! You got it! Up!

965
01:23:41,679 --> 01:23:45,519
Who's that crazy son of a bitch?! Is that Clark?!

966
01:23:45,519 --> 01:23:47,759
I believe it is, sir.

967
01:23:47,759 --> 01:23:50,719
All right, Captain!

968
01:23:50,719 --> 01:23:53,319
We're looking at a court-martial now!

969
01:23:53,319 --> 01:23:55,239
Rotor speed up.

970
01:23:55,239 --> 01:23:57,319
Throttle friction.

971
01:24:00,119 --> 01:24:02,919
Jesus Christ!

972
01:24:02,919 --> 01:24:05,319
When he gets back here, Sergeant,

973
01:24:05,319 --> 01:24:07,239
I'm throwing his ass in the stockade!

974
01:24:07,239 --> 01:24:08,999
We don't have a stockade, sir.

975
01:24:08,999 --> 01:24:10,919
I'll build one!

976
01:24:10,919 --> 01:24:13,359
Son of a bitch!

977
01:24:21,719 --> 01:24:23,159
Good luck, Captain.

978
01:24:37,679 --> 01:24:41,759
All right, all right, all right, here I come.

979
01:25:20,919 --> 01:25:23,319
Chopper Pilot, this is Bat 21.

980
01:25:23,319 --> 01:25:24,759
This is Chopper Pilot,

981
01:25:24,759 --> 01:25:27,119
above your signal on the ninth hole.

982
01:25:27,119 --> 01:25:28,599
Is that you, Birddog?

983
01:25:28,599 --> 01:25:30,119
Yeah, it's me.

984
01:25:30,119 --> 01:25:31,919
Now, let's get you out of here.

985
01:25:31,919 --> 01:25:34,319
50 metres east of you, there's a small field.

986
01:25:34,319 --> 01:25:36,799
If I can get into it, I can make it happen.

987
01:25:36,799 --> 01:25:38,679
Copy that, Bat 21?

988
01:25:38,679 --> 01:25:41,119
I'm on my way, Birddog.

989
01:26:28,119 --> 01:26:32,279
THEY SPEAK IN VIETNAMESE

990
01:26:58,719 --> 01:27:00,559
Down!

991
01:27:17,159 --> 01:27:18,479
- Let's go!
- OK!

992
01:27:29,319 --> 01:27:30,359
Hey!

993
01:27:30,359 --> 01:27:31,959
Hang on!

994
01:27:44,759 --> 01:27:46,279
Hurry up.

995
01:27:53,919 --> 01:27:56,079
All right!

996
01:28:00,959 --> 01:28:03,559
I'm glad to see you, Birddog.

997
01:28:06,279 --> 01:28:09,119
Have a seat, Bat 21.

998
01:28:14,519 --> 01:28:17,239
You'd better check the charts.

999
01:28:17,239 --> 01:28:19,839
I had a hell of a time navigating here.

1000
01:28:22,639 --> 01:28:25,159
GUNFIRE

1001
01:28:25,159 --> 01:28:26,559
Jesus!

1002
01:28:30,319 --> 01:28:32,079
Shit!

1003
01:28:36,919 --> 01:28:39,839
You're losing oil pressure.

1004
01:28:39,839 --> 01:28:41,679
Jesus.

1005
01:28:45,679 --> 01:28:47,799
There's the river.

1006
01:28:47,799 --> 01:28:49,359
We got to make it from here.

1007
01:28:49,359 --> 01:28:52,199
I'm going to have to put this baby down, OK?

1008
01:28:54,799 --> 01:28:57,359
There's a clearing at 9 o'clock.

1009
01:29:31,719 --> 01:29:34,359
Cut into the woods!

1010
01:29:36,159 --> 01:29:38,159
GUNFIRE

1011
01:29:45,519 --> 01:29:47,119
Let's go!

1012
01:30:05,279 --> 01:30:07,679
It's the air strike.

1013
01:30:07,679 --> 01:30:10,959
It's right on time.

1014
01:30:10,959 --> 01:30:11,999
Jesus!

1015
01:30:13,639 --> 01:30:15,399
SHOUTING IN VIETNAMESE

1016
01:30:21,599 --> 01:30:24,359
Go! Move!

1017
01:31:32,919 --> 01:31:35,039
Oh, shit! Goddamn!

1018
01:33:22,839 --> 01:33:24,319
COUGHING

1019
01:34:18,479 --> 01:34:22,319
You know, I've been in the service...

1020
01:34:22,319 --> 01:34:24,759
most of my adult life.

1021
01:34:27,559 --> 01:34:29,999
It's the first time I ever saw any war.

1022
01:34:31,399 --> 01:34:35,279
Guess I was a little closer to the action.

1023
01:34:35,279 --> 01:34:36,719
Aah...

1024
01:34:36,719 --> 01:34:41,519
I've wanted to be a fighter pilot since I was a kid.

1025
01:34:41,519 --> 01:34:44,519
But they wouldn't let me out of the O-2.

1026
01:34:46,039 --> 01:34:47,319
Lucky for me.

1027
01:34:52,959 --> 01:34:55,919
You could have quit anytime.

1028
01:34:57,319 --> 01:34:59,239
Why'd you keep coming back?

1029
01:35:00,679 --> 01:35:03,519
Guess it's the stubborn side of me.

1030
01:35:03,519 --> 01:35:06,439
I started out just doing my job,

1031
01:35:06,439 --> 01:35:08,359
no different from you.

1032
01:35:09,759 --> 01:35:12,359
I hate being told I can't do something.

1033
01:35:12,359 --> 01:35:16,079
I guess that's why I'm still a captain.

1034
01:35:17,959 --> 01:35:19,879
Besides...

1035
01:35:19,879 --> 01:35:23,279
I started feeling what you were going through.

1036
01:35:24,679 --> 01:35:27,439
I heard it in your voice.

1037
01:35:34,239 --> 01:35:35,719
DISTANT RUMBLING

1038
01:35:49,599 --> 01:35:52,239
We're home free, Colonel.

1039
01:35:53,919 --> 01:35:55,839
Yeah.

1040
01:35:55,839 --> 01:35:57,319
HE SIGHS

1041
01:35:58,679 --> 01:36:01,559
Cut the Colonel crap, OK, Birddog?

1042
01:36:01,559 --> 01:36:04,439
It's Iceal Hambleton.

1043
01:36:04,439 --> 01:36:05,879
Iceal?

1044
01:36:05,879 --> 01:36:07,319
Ha-ha-ha!

1045
01:36:07,319 --> 01:36:08,759
Ha-ha-ha!

1046
01:36:08,759 --> 01:36:10,679
It's Hamb.

1047
01:36:10,679 --> 01:36:14,519
Yeah. Hey... Clark Bartholomew.

1048
01:36:14,519 --> 01:36:15,959
Bartholomew?

1049
01:36:15,959 --> 01:36:17,399
Clarky.

1050
01:36:17,399 --> 01:36:19,599
OK.

1051
01:36:35,599 --> 01:36:38,719
- MAN ON RADIO:
- This is USPB-Niner-6.

1052
01:36:38,719 --> 01:36:41,359
We have your boys aboard. Injuries have been treated.

1053
01:36:41,359 --> 01:36:43,639
Will rendezvous with you at base Victor-4.

1054
01:36:43,639 --> 01:36:46,159
This is Niner-6 out.

1055
